Well this giant pied girl has never really liked me 🤷‍♂️ and in this video she finally gets me 😬 not only is she super mom defending her eggs 🥚 but she is only one generation from a wild snake 🐍 making her genes a little more crazy 🧬 regardless she’s a beautiful snake and her babies will be even prettier 😍 
.
.
.

node.text:
MyLove is one of the most beautiful snakes in the 🌍 and looks incredible with the sun hitting her just right ☀️ she’s also the best tempered snake I’ve ever had 😊 so when @sofiedossi asked me to bring her to put her on a blind folded friend we made it happen 🤜 
.
.
.

node.text:
It seems Tripod is everyone’s favorite croc 🐊 and I don’t blame anyone because he’s incredible 😎 looking forward to hopefully visiting him and @mattwright again in the future 😬 but it’s pretty incredible how big that tooth is 😱 the cool thing is just like a shark 🦈 crocs never stop growing back new ones 🦷 so a replacement is coming in right behind this one ☝️ 
.
.
.

Hatching baby pythons is always exciting 🎉 but even more exciting when they’re so rare and look so incredible 😱 these snakes have all sorts of combined genes 🧬 found from the wild and selectively bred to make these amazing snakes 🐍 they look like no other pieds and almost look like leopards 🐆 they’re absolutely beautiful and can’t wait to watch them grow up 🙏
.
.
.

When the big reticulated pythons lay their eggs 🥚 the best thing for the babies and the mom is to remove the eggs 🤷‍♂️ this is because the babies get a higher chance at successfully hatching 🐣 and the mom gets to go back to her normal life quicker 🐍 of course mama doesn’t know I’m trying to help 😬 which can make it interesting 😂 
.
.
.

Set your calendar for two months 📅 because baby children’s pythons will be hatching 🐣 
.
.
.
#reptile #snake #python #childrenspython #eggs #animals #reels #video

Today is a pretty special day I would say super Sunday because one year ago today I lost my foster father on my birthday. Even though I called him uncle Loui I wasn’t actually related to him. I didn’t know one relitive on the planet because I was first adopted as a baby and lost my adopted mom at 4. I would have thought if that wasn’t bad enough then my adopted dad drank himself to death when I was 14 🤷🏽luckily everyone called Loui uncle so when the police came to let him know my father had passed they didn’t take me away to a foster home but thought he was my relative ( I would have never made it! ) It would have been a nightmare given all my issues including learning issues. School wasn’t working for me to say the least but luckily uncle Loui let me move in and just pay my food and rent and over time he became a great role model and one of the most amazing people I have ever met. He would help anyone and did just that. The next 40 years he was part of every part of my life even helping me and my wife’s with our three daughters as we all worked so hard to create what you know today as the @thereptilezoo the details are nothing short of amazing. God has had his hand on the whole thing reminding me the whole way right down to Uncle Loui passing on my birthday and sharing the same birthday with me.  I use to think I was so unlucky and life had given me such a bad hand but now I realize the road to where I am today was a product of the hard times preparing me for the troubles ahead so that I could conquer the giant problems ahead and having him in my life would have never happened if the world had not fallen all around me. It was well worth every storm that came my way. Never giving up sounds like a slogan but I can tell you the rewards are much greater than the trophies that come by the perseverance that it took. Hope you have an amazing day and remember to enjoy your friendships and family everyday (ps I found my whole family and that’s a whole other story 🤯 yep the term living the dream is mind blowing in my life)

.
.
.

It seems Tripod is everyone’s favorite croc 🐊 and I don’t blame anyone because he’s incredible 😎 looking forward to hopefully visiting him and @mattwright again in the future 😬 but it’s pretty incredible how big that tooth is 😱 the cool thing is just like a shark 🦈 crocs never stop growing back new ones 🦷 so a replacement is coming in right behind this one ☝️ 
.
.
.
